This is a review paper on Brain Computer Interfaces (BCIs) studies using Virtual Reality (VR).
It groups 83 papers that used a combination of BCIs and VR to study diverse aspects: classification, neuromarkers etc.
The paper is organized as follows:
1. Abstract
2. Introduction
3. Theoretical (Theories of Cybersickness)
4. Methodology
5. Results
6. Discussion
7. Conclusion
